## 🧭 Layout Component

### 📍 Location
`client/src/components/Layout.js`

### 🚀 Features
- Top navigation bar with links to:
  - Dashboard (`/`)
  - Agent Configurator (`/agents`)
  - Results & Insights (`/results`)
- Logout button that:
  - Clears `localStorage` token
  - Redirects to `/login`
- Renders nested routes via `<Outlet />`

### 🧱 Code Structure

```tsx
import { Link, Outlet, useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';
import {
  AppBar,
  Toolbar,
  Button,
  Container,
  Box
} from '@mui/material';
import LogoutOutlinedIcon from '@mui/icons-material/LogoutOutlined';
```

### 🔗 Navigation Links

```tsx
const navLinks = [
  { to: '/', label: 'Dashboard' },
  { to: '/agents', label: 'Agent Configurator' },
  { to: '/results', label: 'Results & Insights' },
];
```

### 🔐 Logout Button

Styled with Material UI and includes an icon:

```tsx
<Button
  variant="outlined"
  color="error"
  startIcon={<LogoutOutlinedIcon />}
  onClick={() => {
    localStorage.removeItem('token');
    navigate('/login');
  }}
>
  Logout
</Button>
```

### 🧩 Outlet Usage

Renders child routes inside a styled container:

```tsx
<Container sx={{ mt: 4 }}>
  <Outlet />
</Container>
```

